The paper deals with resource estimation for SQL queries, which is a core problem in database systems. Therefore, cs.DB (Database) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes the use of statistical techniques for resource estimation, which falls under the purview of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the modeling of individual operators, which is a problem in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper validates its approach using real-life and benchmark workloads, which is a problem in cs.SE (Software Engineering).
